ign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Proposal for a New Officer Position</span><hr size=1> I was wondering what everyone thought about the idea of a Treasury position that was responsible for collecting funds for the operation of guild activities (ie. recruitment events, internal guild activities, purchasing rare equip through the distribution of funds for the betterment of the guild, equip for pledge memebers, ceremonies, etc.) Since RL is so drive by the all mighty dollar for handling day to day business, why not EQ?  It seems by having money available, makes events more concrete and not as abstract.  The person would be responsible for collecting funds from other memebers and placed in a seperate guild account.  Allocation of those funds would need to be discussed and approved by 2/3 of a majority vote by the officers for removal of those funds ensuring that a minimum balance needs to be maintained.  Since we are targeting level 10 and up, money shouldn't be that big of probelem even if it is as little as 5 pp per month from everyone.  If someone has a big concern, then we can work with them. Just some ideas that I thought would help in our restructuring the hierarchy of BO.  Let me know what you think.<br>
<br>
Ndyira<br>
